replyContent: Hi Emily, do you have Android 4.4 KitKat?  Users have alerted me to the fact that this version of Android no longer supports writing files to the SD card in the usual Music directory.  I'm currently investigating solutions. Please contact me at daniel.bigham@gmail.com if possible. Thanks.

content: Hassle free ..thank you..

replyContent:
Hi Jacob,

Android phone manufacturers can be a bit inconsistent about the SD card location. Please send an email and I'll work with you to fix that for your model of phone. Good thoughts about adding a way to stop the sync and exit the app, I'll try and add that.

5/24/14- (Let me put this review "on hold" for right now.  it worked the first day but now it is giving me problems). I've been through several apps to sync my Android to iTunes.
